On March 18, 2016, the President signed several bills into law. These include H.R. 1755, which amends the charter of the Disabled American Veterans; S. 1172, the "Edward 'Ted' Kaufman and Michael Leavitt Presidential Transitions Improvements Act of 2015," which establishes transition councils for efficient transfer of power; S. 1580, the "Competitive Service Act of 2015," which allows agencies to share lists of eligible employees; S. 1826, which designates a post office in Wisconsin; and S. 2426, which directs the Secretary of State to develop a strategy for Taiwan's observer status at international meetings.